# Normalize line endings to LF for all text files.
#
# Without this file, each environment's git config (core.autocrlf) decides
# how line endings are handled independently — Windows checks out CRLF,
# Linux/macOS expect LF, and the same working copy shows a sea of false
# "changes" when opened in a Linux devcontainer mounted from a Windows host.
#
# With `text=auto eol=lf`: git stores LF in the repo, checks out LF on
# every platform, and normalizes on commit. Result: identical working
# copies regardless of where the repo is cloned or opened.

* text=auto eol=lf
